  "text": "Muscles that must work against gravity, such as the soleus, gastrocnemius, and vastus lateralis, are most commonly adversely affected by immobilization [CITATION_1] . Their fibers undergo apoptosis during atrophy, especially the soleus, which primarily consists of slow-twitch fibers. The soleus responds rapidly to disuse and can undergo fiber-type switching. Generalized skeletal muscle atrophy involves decreased protein production and cross-sectional area (CSA), which contribute to reduced force production.",
